  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Synergy for Social Cohesion Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contributing to the National strategy implementation for unity and Reconciliation commission.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Alert will offer the technical and accompaniment support to national unity and reconciliation commission in designing the capacity building plan and rolling it out to the targeted districts and groups that would directly contribute to the implementation of unity and reconciliation commission. The implementation will be done jointly by both International alert and NURC but Alert will take the lead when it comes to implementation, donor reporting and monitoring and evaluation for this activities. International Alert will work closely with the selected district in this pilot phase to ensure that all key people</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will develop and implement a comprehensive capacity building plan which will assist the Rwandan government and other development actors in mainstreaming national reconciliation, peace building and social cohesion to promote the culture of peace and sustainable development. This will enable all actors in development to proactively engage with citizens and sensitize them on the mutual impact of peace and development. The project will allow for conflict prevention to be mainstreamed into local structures and processes that encourage a culture of peace, in which conflicts are addressed before they degenerate into violence, and in which local government officers as well as civil society members have access to tools that allow them to prevent, manage, and resolve conflicts</narrative>
  </description>
